<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2864] add maxtf to fieldinvertstate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2864</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;the maximum within-document TF is a very useful scoring value, &lt;br/&gt;
we should expose it so that people can use it in scoring&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;consider the following sim:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
@Override
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; idf(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; docFreq, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; numDocs) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; 1.0F; /* not used */
}

@Override
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; computeNorm(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; field, FieldInvertState state) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; state.getBoost() / (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.sqrt(state.getMaxTF());
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which is surprisingly effective, but more interesting for practical reasons.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
